
HTML Form -
- Form is most IMP & powerful in HTML without of HTML ingnore.
- Data send to server using Form - Get Input from user & ready to send in server.

Q. - How to forms ?
=>

Shortcut - form + tab

E.g. Form element
    <form action="">
            
      </form>

*NOTE :- All over form info like name, phono, email.. etc. make bundle of it & send to backend server. 


action - url

method -
2 types of form we can denote through methods -
1] get 
    - data visible in website URL.
    - all information go in clear text format.
	
2] post 
    - all data you can submit in the server we perfer post method
    - in post method data can send in encrypt mode.

input elements -

Shortcut - input:text
E.g. -
     <input type="text" name="" id="">
	 
input element attribute - placeholder
E.g. -
     <input type="text" placeholder="first name" id="">
	 

*NOTE :- In screen readers, google search engine not only use placeholders
       - we use good practice is we use label tag with every input.
	   
label tag -

- With every input we use label tag
- Screen reader also best way to known whats info in below.

*NOTE :- Also known through this info through placeholders but, screen reader can't read placeholders.

for tag -

- for tag shows association between with which inputs?
- highlight input field i.e. its denotes which input for which input. 


E.g. - 
	<label for="fname">First Name</label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="first name" id="fname">



E.g.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <title>Forms one</title>
      <style>
      body{
            background-color: #414141;
            color: #ffffff;
            
      }</style>
</head>
<body>
      <h1>Forms in HTML</h1>
      <form action="" method="GET" accept-charset="utf-8" autocomplete="" enctype="" >
            <label for="fname">First Name</label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="first name" id="fname">

            <label for="lname">Last Name</label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="last name" id="lname">

            <button type="submit">Pay</button>
      </form>
</body>
</html>




